TextBody:
ref:_00D7091pB._500Q000Nv3IT:ref

After setting "Restart Incomplete Scans after" and "Rescan unimported hosts after" to 0, the "SEEK System Scans" job now completes successfully. However, when running the Bulk Import job, I still encounter the same error:

Netwrix.CoordinationLibrary.Processes.FSAABulkImportProcess | Sequence contains no elements.

Additionally, when I enable the "Enable file system scan streaming" option, I receive the following warning:

Netwrix.CoordinationLibrary.Processes.FSAAScanProcess | There is FSAA data that needs to be imported, disabling streaming. Bulk import will have to be run after this scan.

It seems the scan detects data that should be imported, but the bulk import process fails consistently with the same error. I would appreciate your guidance on how to proceed and resolve this issue.
Subject: Netwrix Support Ticket #441641 - AIQON | Assistance Required for Sensitive Data Collection on File Server

Ticket Number: 00441641 Ticket Subject: AIQON | Assistance Required for Sensitive Data Collection on File Server Ticket Details: Hello, I need assistance with collecting sensitive data on my file server. I'm able to successfully collect activity, permissions, and other general information. However, when it comes to sensitive data, the application encounters several errors. In the "SEEK System Scans" job, I receive the following message: Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.FSAA.AppletDeployment | No need to scan, Tier 2 DB USN is greater than Tier 1 DB USN, needs bulk import. Based on the documentation, I unchecked the two boxes under the query in "Scan Settings" — "Restart Incomplete Scans after" and "Rescan unimported hosts after" — but the same error persists. I also tried changing the hosts, using the local server, and selecting all hosts, but none of these approaches worked. In the "SEEK Bulk Import" job, which should be running, I consistently get the following error: Netwrix.CoordinationLibrary.Processes.FSAABulkImportProcess | Sequence contains no elements. I’ve attempted changing the hosts here as well, but the issue remains the same. Note: I recently upgraded Netwrix Access Analyzer to version 12.0, and I couldn’t find the Sensitive Data Discovery module in this version. Could you please assist me with this case? I’ve attached the error logs generated in the output folders for your review. Thank you in advance. Best regards, Gustavo Rossato Thank you!
